In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. discusses the importance and value of America's national parks. He highlights the impact these parks have on individuals, including himself and his family, by providing healing and inspiration. President Biden emphasizes the responsibility to ensure that national parks are inclusive and serve all communities. He mentions recent additions to the National Park System that reflect a commitment to support marginalized groups. The President also acknowledges the need for continued work to bring equity to the parks and to collaborate with Tribal Nations. He proclaims April 17-25, 2021, as National Park Week, encouraging Americans to visit and enjoy the benefits of spending time in nature while practicing responsible recreation and following COVID-19 safety guidelines.